- `programming_language` — python, go, sql
- `framework` — react, spring, .net
- `software` — excel, photoshop, sap, epic-ehr, westlaw
- `tool` — catch-all when neither software nor equipment fits
- `equipment` — CNC lathe, MRI scanner, forklift, commercial kitchen, scaffolding
- `credential` — RN license, CPA, forklift cert, bar admission, GxP
- `domain_knowledge` — tax law, pediatric oncology, supply chain, HACCP
- `methodology` — agile, lean, ITIL, GxP, waterfall
- `soft_skill` — communication, leadership, client-handling
- `physical_ability` — lift 50 lbs, stand 8 hrs, colour vision

Spoken languages go in `required_languages` (ISO-639-1), never in `required_skills`.
